{{/*
  users.acl - the external DragonFly ACL file (--aclfile in the flagfile). Go text/template
  strict (ADR-010). .vars.users - a MAP name→{perms, state, password}, assembled by the
  scenario; password is resolved keeper-side from Vault (ADR-012). DF accepts the redis
  aclfile format, including a hashed password `#<sha256hex>` (DF acl/user.cc
  SetPasswordHash is_hashed).

  ORDER DETERMINISM (templating.md §6): range over a MAP walks keys SORTED →
  lines are stable across runs (no false change → no extra onchanges restart, which
  would cascade across a rolling-restart fleet). Passing a list would inherit the
  non-deterministic order of Go map iteration (that was exactly the tiling-critical bug).

  Line format (Redis ACL convention, DF-compatible):
    user <name> <state> #<sha256(password)> <perms>
  The password is written as a HASH (#<sha256hex>, sprig sha256sum), NOT plaintext: even if
  the file leaks, the original password cannot be recovered, and DF accepts #<hash> on par
  with >password.

  ★ default_admin REDESIGN: --requirepass is REMOVED from the flagfile - all authentication
  (including internal: replication/sentinel/health-PING) goes through the SYSTEM user
  default_admin (`~* &* +@all`). default_admin comes from the .vars.users MAP via range,
  like the other system users (replica/monitoring/sentinel/haproxy) - it's added to
  essence.system_acl_users, and the scenario adds it to users with its OWN Vault password.

  ★ The built-in DragonFly `default` user → `off`, IF the operator did NOT declare it in
  input.users: the built-in default is no longer needed (its role is taken by default_admin),
  but with --aclfile set, DF would otherwise leave the built-in default reachable without a
  password. So if `default` is NOT present in .vars.users (the operator didn't declare it) -
  we render an EXPLICIT `user default off` (a disabled default, a safe default). If the
  operator DID declare default in input.users - it ends up in .vars.users (operator-extra)
  and is rendered by the range below like a regular user (its state/perms), and the explicit
  off line is NOT added (`index .vars.users "default"` on a missing MAP key returns nil
  without an error in strict-mode, built-in text/template; hasKey is NOT in the sprig
  allowlist - shared/tmpl/sprig.go).

  Minimum valid file - default_admin (system, always) + `user default off`.
*/}}
{{- if not (index .vars.users "default") }}
user default off
{{- end }}
{{- range $name, $u := .vars.users }}
user {{ $name }} {{ $u.state }} #{{ $u.password | sha256sum }} {{ $u.perms }}
{{- end }}
